ISSUED AT 0600 MONDAY 08 DECEMBER 2014
1. GALE WARNING: SOUTHERLY GALES OR STRONG GALES WILL DEVELOP OVERNIGHT
AND TOMORROW MORNING ON ALL IRISH COASTAL WATERS AND ON THE IRISH SEA.
SMALL CRAFT WARNING: NORTHWESTERLY WINDS WILL REACH FORCE 6 OR 7 THIS MORNING
ON ALL IRISH COASTAL WATERS.
2. METEOROLOGICAL SITUATION AT 0600: A COLD UNSTABLE NORTHWESTERLY AIRFLOW
COVERS IRELAND. A TRANSIENT RIDGE WILL BUILD THIS AFTERNOON AND EVENING.
A STRENGTHENING SOUTHERLY AIRFLOW WILL DEVELOP OVERNIGHT AS A WARM FRONT
MOVES IN FROM THE ATLANTIC. THIS IS ASSOCIATED WITH A VIGOROUS DEPRESSION
MOVING FROM THE SOUTH OF GREENLAND.
3. FORECAST FOR ALL IRISH COASTAL WATERS AND FOR THE IRISH SEA:
WIND: NORTHWESTERLY FORCE 6 OR 7 GUSTING TO GALE FORCE 8 NEAR SHOWERS FOR
A TIME THIS MORNING. BACKING WESTERLY THIS AFTERNOON AND EVENING FORCE 4
OR 5. FURTHER BACKING SOUTH TO SOUTHWEST TONIGHT AND INCREASING FORCE 7 TO
GALE FORCE 8.
WEATHER: SQUALLY SHOWERS/ISOLATED THUNDERSTORMS BECOMING GENERALLY FAIR.
PATCHY RAIN/DRIZZLE TONIGHT.
VISIBILITY: POOR IN SHOWERS. BECOMING LOCALLY MODERATE TONIGHT.
3A. WARNING OF HEAVY SWELL: TODAY ON WESTERN AND NORTHERN COASTS.
4. OUTLOOK FOR A FURTHER 24 HOURS UNTIL 0600 WEDNESDAY 10 DECEMBER 2014:
GALE TO STRONG GALE FORCE SOUTH TO SOUTHWEST WINDS. LATER VEERING WESTERLY.
INCREASING TO STORM FORCE 10 ON WESTERN AND NORTHERN COASTS. RAIN LATER
